==English==

===Etymology===
Stands for ''violence chip'', coined by Tim Collings.

===Noun===
'''V-chip'''

# A form of [[censorship]], or rather [[censorware]], promoted by the William Jefferson Clinton Administration and devised by Tim Collings as a way to allow parents to control the level of objectionable content that their children may see on television.

===Translations===
'''censorship device'''
*Chinese: [[V 芯片]] (V xinpian)
*French: [[V-morceau]]
*Japanese: [[Vチップ]]
*Spanish: [[V-viruta]]

